Joining data frames ::: {.cell layout-align="center"} ```{.r .cell-code} something_join(x, y) ``` ::: - `left_join()`: all rows from x - `right_join()`: all rows from y - `full_join()`: all rows from both x and y - `semi_join()`: all rows from x where there are matching values in y, keeping just columns from x - `inner_join()`: all rows from x where there are matching values in y, return all combination of multiple matches in the case of multiple matches - `anti_join()`: return all rows from x where there are not matching values in y, never duplicate rows of x - ... --- ##
